---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout
  title="robots.txt For AI Agents | Is It Agent Ready?"
  description="Learn how to configure robots.txt for AI agents, sitemap discovery, and crawler-specific rules like GPTBot, Claude-Web, and Google-Extended."
  canonical="https://isitagentready.com/checks/robots-txt"
>
  <section class="card" style="padding: 28px;">
    <h1 class="section-title">robots.txt for AI agents</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      A valid `robots.txt` file remains the first discovery surface for search crawlers and AI agents. It should declare crawl rules,
      point to your sitemap, and optionally include AI-specific user-agent directives.
    </p>
    <h2>Why it matters</h2>
    <ul class="clean">
      <li>Helps agents find important content quickly.</li>
      <li>Lets you define AI-specific access policy instead of relying only on wildcard rules.</li>
      <li>Acts as the normal place to advertise sitemap URLs.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Example</h2>
    <pre>{`User-agent: *
Allow: /

User-agent: GPTBot
Allow: /

User-agent: Claude-Web
Allow: /

Content-Signal: ai-train=no, search=yes, ai-input=yes
Sitemap: https://example.com/sitemap.xml`}</pre>
    <p class="muted">
      Related docs:
      <a class="link" href="https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9309" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> RFC 9309</a>
      {' · '}
      <a class="link" href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/ai-crawl-control/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Cloudflare AI Crawl Control</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
